wwpModulesEsm.name: wwpModulesEsm

revisions.description: Added alertCustomNBINotification for normalized trap forwarding.
Increased size of alertentity and alertObjectType. Fixed to typos.
Added ipAddressAddrType and ipAddressAddr for MO and Alert notifications

wwpESMFreeMemory.description: The Free memory available in the device in which the WWP ESM is running

wwpESMStartTime.name: wwpESMStartTime
wwpESMStartTime.description: This variable states the time at which the ESM Server started

wwpESMUpTime.name: wwpESMUpTime
wwpESMUpTime.description: This variable states the duration for which the ESM Server has been running

wwpESMShutdown.name: wwpESMShutdown
wwpESMShutdown.description: This variable is used to shutdown the ESM from the manager. The user needs to give the login name and the password.Once,the user gives the loginname and the password,the ESM Server shuts down. SYNTAX: loginName,password

wwpESMSchedulerIndex.description: The index for the WWP ESM Scheduler instance

wwpESMSchedulerIdleThreads.name: wwpESMSchedulerIdleThreads
wwpESMSchedulerIdleThreads.description: The number of idle Worker threads

moUserPropNames.name: moUserPropNames
moUserPropNames.description: This variable indicates to the agent what all user property values the user would like to see in the moUserProp variable of the MoTable. This also provides for the facility of viewing all the user property-values by specifying the word 'all' . If the user needs to see only a few specific user property values ,then he needs to specify them explicitly SYNTAX1 all SYNTAX2 userPropName1,userPropName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPopName2=value2..

moNameIndex.name: moNameIndex
moNameIndex.description: This variable represents the name of the Network Element. This name should uniquely represent the MO in the network domain across all MO types.This entry corresponds to the Name field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moOwnerName.name: moOwnerName
moOwnerName.description: This variable represents the Ownername of the Network Element. This name also uniquely represents the MO in the network domain across all MO types. This entry corresponds to the OwnerName field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moType.name: moType
moType.description: This variable represents the type of the Network Element whose attributes are presented in this specific row of the MO table.This entry corresponds to the Type field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moFailureCount.name: moFailureCount
moFailureCount.description: This variable represents the number of failures occuring in the network element. This entry corresponds to the FailureCount field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moFailureThreshold.name: moFailureThreshold
moFailureThreshold.description: This variable represents the minimum value for failures which acts as the threshold.This entry corresponds to the FailureThreshold field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moManaged.name: moManaged
moManaged.description: This variable states whether the mo is managed or not.This entry corresponds to the Managed field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moStatus.name: moStatus
moStatus.description: This value gives the current status of the MO.This entry corresponds to the Status field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moStatusChangeTime.name: moStatusChangeTime
moStatusChangeTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the status of the mo was formally acknowledged to have changed.This entry corresponds to the StatusChangeTime field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moStatusUpdateTime.name: moStatusUpdateTime
moStatusUpdateTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the status of the mo was formally acknowledged to have been updated.This entry corresponds to the StatusUpdateTime field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moPollInterval.name: moPollInterval
moPollInterval.description: This variable states the polling interval of the mo.This entry corresponds to the PollInterval field of the ManagedObject table in the database

moUserProperties.name: moUserProperties
moUserProperties.description: The values for the user properties which the user specifies in the moUserPropNames variable are displayed The values will be displayed in the folloing formate propName1=value1,porpName2=vaule2,....

moDerivedProperties.name: moDerivedProperties
moDerivedProperties.description: This variable displays the values of the user defined objects ' properties which the user specifies in the derivedPropNames variable in the moDerivedPropNamesTable. The values will be displayed in the following formate propName1=value1,propName2=value2,....

inheritingOid1.name: inheritingOid1
inheritingOid1.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is derived from TopoObject, then, the oid of the TopoObjectTable in this MIB will be filled here.If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

moTable.name: moTable
moTable.description: This describes the details of Managed Objects

moEntry.name: moEntry
moEntry.description: An entry of the Mo Table

inheritingTableName1.name: inheritingTableName1
inheritingTableName1.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is derived from TopoObject, then, the table name TopoObjectTable will be filled here.If the tablename is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

ipAddress.name: ipAddress
ipAddress.description: This variable states the ipAddress of the Object.This entry corresponds to the IpAddress field of the TopoObject table in the database

netmask.name: netmask
netmask.description: This variable states the net mask of the object.This entry corresponds to the NetMask field of the TopoObject table in the database

moCommunity.name: moCommunity
moCommunity.description: This variable states the read community String used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an SnmpNode.This entry corresponds to the Community field of the TopoObject table in the database

moWriteCommunity.name: moWriteCommunity
moWriteCommunity.description: This variable states the write community String used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an SnmpNode.This entry corresponds to the WriteCommunity field of the TopoObject table in the database

snmpPort.name: snmpPort
snmpPort.description: This variable states the Snmp port used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an Snmp Node.This entry corresponds to the SnmpPort field of the TopoObject table in the database

isDHCP.name: isDHCP
isDHCP.description: This variable states whether the network element supports DHCP (i.e is the ipaddress for the network element assigned by DHCP protocol). This entry corresponds to the IsDHCP field of the TopoObject table in the database

baseMibs.name: baseMibs
baseMibs.description: This variable states the Mibs implemented by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This field is valid only if the Network Element is also an Snmp Node.This entry corresponds to the BaseMibs field of the TopoObject table in the database

version.name: version
version.description: This variable states the version used by the Snmp Agent in the Network Element. This entry corresponds to the Version field of the TopoObject table in the database.

userName.name: userName
userName.description: This variable states the userName used by the SNMPv3 Agent in the Network Element. This entry corresponds to the UserName field of the TopoObject table in the database.

contextName.name: contextName
contextName.description: This variable states the contextName used by the SNMPv3 Agent in the Network Element. This entry corresponds to the ContextName field of the TopoObject table in the database.

inheritingOid2.name: inheritingOid2
inheritingOid2.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either Node or any of its child, then, the oid of the NodeTable in this MIB will be filled here.If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

topoObjTable.name: topoObjTable
topoObjTable.description: This table contains the various topo Objects

topoObjEntry.name: topoObjEntry
topoObjEntry.description: An entry of the topoObject Table

inheritingTableName2.name: inheritingTableName2
inheritingTableName2.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either Node or any of its child, then, the table name NodeTable will be filled here.If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

discover.name: discover
discover.description: This variable states whether disocvery is being done on this network or not. This entry corresponds to the Discover field of the Network table in the database

discoverStatus.name: discoverStatus
discoverStatus.description: This variable states the discovery status for the network. This entry corresponds to the DiscoveryStatus field of the Network table in the database

inheritingOid3.name: inheritingOid3
inheritingOid3.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MyNetworkChild) of Network (or any child of MyNetworkChild),then, the oid of the direct child's table (e.g. MyNetworkChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here, If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

networkTable.name: networkTable
networkTable.description: This table contains information about the various networks supported by the ESM

networkEntry.name: networkEntry
networkEntry.description: An entry of the Network table

inheritingTableName3.name: inheritingTableName3
inheritingTableName3.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MyNetworkChild) of Network (or any child of MyNetworkChild),then, the tablename of the direct child's table (e.g. MyNetworkChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here, If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

isRouter.name: isRouter
isRouter.description: This variable states whether the node is a router or not. This entry corresponds to the isRouter field of the Node table in the database

inheritingOid4.name: inheritingOid4
inheritingOid4.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpNode or any of its child, then, the oid of the SnmpNodeTable in this MIB will be filled here. If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

nodeTable.name: nodeTable
nodeTable.description: This table describes the nodes in the ESM

nodeEntry.name: nodeEntry
nodeEntry.description: An entry of the Node table

inheritingTableName4.name: inheritingTableName4
inheritingTableName4.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpNode or any of its child, then, the tabel name SnmpNodeTable will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

ipAddressTable.name: ipAddressTable
ipAddressTable.description: This table describes the ipAddress objects

ipAddressEntry.name: ipAddressEntry
ipAddressEntry.description: An entry of the ipAddress table

parentNode.name: parentNode
parentNode.description: This variable states the parent Node of this Interface.This entry corresponds to the ParentNode field of the IpAddress table in the database.

parentNet.name: parentNet
parentNet.description: This variable states the name of the parent network to which this Interface belongs. This entry corresponds to the ParentNode field of the IpAddress table in the database.

inheritingOid5.name: inheritingOid5
inheritingOid5.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpInterface or any of its child.Then,the oid of the SnmpInterfaceTable in this MIB will be filled here. If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

inheritingTableName5.name: inheritingTableName5
inheritingTableName5.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object's type is either SnmpInterface or any of its child.Then,the tabelname SnmpInterfaceTable will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

hostNetMask.name: hostNetMask
hostNetMask.description: This variable states the netmask of the primary interface reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the HostNetMask field of the SnmpNode table in the database

sysDesc.name: sysDesc
sysDesc.description: This variable states the System Descriptor of this node as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the SysDescr field of the SnmpNode table in the database

sysName.name: sysName
sysName.description: This variable states the System Name of this node as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the SysName field of the SnmpNode table in the database

sysOid.name: sysOid
sysOid.description: This variable states the System Object Identifier of this node as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the SysOid field of the SnmpNode table in the database

inheritingOid6.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child ( e.g. MySnmpNodeChild) of SnmpNode (or any child of MySnmpNodeChild),then, the oid of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpNodeChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. snmpNodeTable.name: snmpNodeTable
snmpNodeTable.description: This table describes the SNMP nodes in the WWP ESM

snmpNodeEntry.name: snmpNodeEntry
snmpNodeEntry.description: An entry of the snmpNode table

inheritingTableName6.name: inheritingTableName6
inheritingTableName6.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child ( e.g. MySnmpNodeChild) of SnmpNode (or any child of MySnmpNodeChild),then, the table name of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpNodeChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

hostnetMask.name: hostnetMask
hostnetMask.description: This variable states the netmask of this interface reported by the snmp agent in the node to which this interface object is attahced. This entry corresponds to the HostNetMask field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

ifIndex.name: ifIndex
ifIndex.description: This variable states the interface index reported by the snmp agent in the node to which this interface object is attached. This entry corresponds to the IfIndex field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

physMedia.name: physMedia
physMedia.description: This variable states the physical media of this inetrface as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the PhysMedia field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

physAddress.name: physAddress
physAddress.description: This variable states the Physical address of the interface as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the PhysAddr field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

ifSpeed.name: ifSpeed
ifSpeed.description: This variable states the speed of this interface as reported by the snmp agent.This entry corresponds to the IfSpeed field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

ifDesc.name: ifDesc
ifDesc.description: This variable states the descriptor of this inetrface as reported by the snmp agent. This entry corresponds to the IfDescr field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

sysOID.name: sysOID
sysOID.description: This variable states the System Object Identifier of this node as reported by the snmp agent.This entry corresponds to the SysOid field of the SnmpInterface table in the database

inheritingOid7.name: inheritingOid7
inheritingOid7.description: This variable states the oid of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChild) of SnmpInterface (or any child of MySnmpInterfaceChild),then, the oid of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. If the oid is .0.0 then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

snmpInterfaceTable.name: snmpInterfaceTable
snmpInterfaceTable.description: This table describes the properties of the snmp interfaces attached to a Snmp node disocvered by the WWP ESM system.

inheritingTableName7.name: inheritingTableName7
inheritingTableName7.description: This variable states the name of the table. For example,if the discovered object is any direct child( e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChild) of SnmpInterface (or any child of MySnmpInterfaceChild),then, the table name of the direct child's table(e.g. MySnmpInterfaceChildTable) in this MIB will be filled here. If the table name is empty then it implies that there is no further inheritance.

indexNum.name: indexNum
indexNum.description: This variable is an incremental integer which uniquely identifies each entry of the table.

objClassName.name: objClassName
objClassName.description: This variable indicates the class name of the user defined objects and identifies them uniquely.The user needs to specify the full package name of the object For example : com.adventnet.nms.topodb.Node

derivedPropNames.name: derivedPropNames
derivedPropNames.description: This variable indicates the names of the derived properties of user defined objects which will be displayed in the moDerivedProperties variable in the MoTable. The user must specify the names of derived properties in the following format .SYNTAX: propName1,propName2,...

tableOid.name: tableOid
tableOid.description: This variable states the oid of the table for the particular mo-type

tableName.name: tableName
tableName.description: This variable describes the table name

moDerivedPropNameTable.name: moDerivedPropNameTable
moDerivedPropNameTable.description: This table contains the type of the user-defined objects and the properties of the user defined objects. The user can specify what all user-object's properties he wants to be displayed in the moDerivedProperties in MO table.

moDerivedPropNameEntry.name: moDerivedPropNameEntry
moDerivedPropNameEntry.description: An entry of the User Object Table.

wwpESMNumEvents.name: wwpESMNumEvents
wwpESMNumEvents.description: The total Number of Events in the WWP ESM system

wwpESMNumAlerts.name: wwpESMNumAlerts
wwpESMNumAlerts.description: The total Number of Alerts in the WWP ESM system

wwpESMEventsInBuffer.name: wwpESMEventsInBuffer
wwpESMEventsInBuffer.description: The Size of the Event Queue in the WWP ESM system

wwpESMAlertsInBuffer.name: wwpESMAlertsInBuffer
wwpESMAlertsInBuffer.description: The Size of the Alert Queue in the WWP ESM system

alertUserPropNames.name: alertUserPropNames
alertUserPropNames.description: This variable indicates to the agent what all user property values the user would like to see in the alertUserProperties variable of the AlertTable This also provides for the facility of viewing all the user property-values by specifying the word 'all' . If the user needs to see only a few specific user property values ,then he needs to specify them explicitly SYNTAX1 all SYNTAX2 userPropName1,userPropName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2..

eventUserPropNames.name: eventUserPropNames
eventUserPropNames.description: This variable indicates to the agent what all user properties value the user would like to see in the eventUserProperties variable in the EventTable This also provides for the facility of viewing all the user property-values by specifying the word 'all' . If the user needs to see only a few specific user property values ,then he needs to specify them explicitly SYNTAX1 all SYNTAX2 userPropName1,userPropName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2..

alertEntity.name: alertEntity
alertEntity.description: This variable states the unique source of the alert which uniquely identifies any alert in the table.This corresponds to the Entity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertOwnerName.name: alertOwnerName
alertOwnerName.description: This variable states the name of the owner of the alert.This corresponds to the OwnerName entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertCreateTime.name: alertCreateTime
alertCreateTime.description: This variable states the time of creation of the alert.This corresponds to the CreateTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertSource.name: alertSource
alertSource.description: This variable indicates the source of the alert i.e., from where the alert generated.This corresponds to the Source entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertModTime.name: alertModTime
alertModTime.description: This variable states the latest time at which the alert status was modified.This corresponds to the ModTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertSeverity.name: alertSeverity
alertSeverity.description: This variable describes the severity of the alert in integer format.This corresponds to the Severity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertPreviousSeverity.name: alertPreviousSeverity
alertPreviousSeverity.description: This variable states the previous severity of the alert.This corresponds to the PreviousSeverity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertCategory.name: alertCategory
alertCategory.description: This variable describes the category to which the alert belongs to, in a string form.This corresponds to the Category entry in the Alert Table in the database

alertUserProperties.name: alertUserProperties
alertUserProperties.description: This variable describes the values ot the user properties which the user specifies in the alertUserPropNames variable in the alert table. The values will be displayed in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2,...

alertTable.name: alertTable
alertTable.description: This table describes all the elements of the alert. This table has been deprecated since the AlertSource column is not an index column. This table has been replaced by AlarmTable.

alertEntry.name: alertEntry
alertEntry.description: An entry of the alert table

evtID.name: evtID
evtID.description: This variable is the unique id (primary key) of this event object.This corresponds to the Id entry in the Event Table in the database

evtSource.name: evtSource
evtSource.description: This variable is the source of the event.This corresponds to the Source entry in the Event Table in the database

evtEntity.name: evtEntity
evtEntity.description: This variable is the Entity (also known as Failure Object) of the Event.This corresponds to the Entity entry in the Event Table in the database

evtSeverity.name: evtSeverity
evtSeverity.description: This variable is the Severity of the Event object.This corresponds to the Severity entry in the Event Table in the database

evtCategory.name: evtCategory
evtCategory.description: This variable gives the category of the event, like Topology events or Threshold event etc. This corresponds to the Category entry in the Event Table in the database

evtTime.name: evtTime
evtTime.description: This variable is the time of occurrence (creation), in milliseconds, of this Event object. This corresponds to the Ttime entry in the Event Table in the database

evtText.name: evtText
evtText.description: This variable gives the descriptive text message of the event.This corresponds to the Text entry in the Event Table in the database

eventUserProperties.name: eventUserProperties
eventUserProperties.description: This variable describes the values ot the user properties which the user specifies in the eventUserPropNames variable The values will be displayed in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2,...

eventTable.name: eventTable
eventTable.description: This table describes the events in the event database

eventEntry.name: eventEntry
eventEntry.description: An entry of the event Table

severityName.name: severityName
severityName.description: This variable displays the name of severity like critical,major,minor etc.

numberOfAlarms.name: numberOfAlarms
numberOfAlarms.description: This variable displays the number of alarms of a particular severity.

wwpESMSeverityTable.name: wwpESMSeverityTable
wwpESMSeverityTable.description: This table shows the number of alarms of a particular severity.

alarmTable.name: alarmTable
alarmTable.description: This table describes various attributes of the ESM alarms. This is the replacement table for alertTable.This table has the following features other than those found in alertTable: 1. AlarmSource added as the first index along with AlarmOwnerName and AlarmEntity. 2. AlarmAssignedTo - a new column to describe the owner to whom the alarm assigned.

alarmSource.name: alarmSource
alarmSource.description: This variable indicates the source of the alarm i.e.,from where the alarm generated. This corresponds to the Source entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmOwnerName.name: alarmOwnerName
alarmOwnerName.description: This variable states the OwnerName for the alarm.This corresponds to the OwnerName entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmEntity.name: alarmEntity
alarmEntity.description: This variable states the unique name of each alarm which is used to identifies any alarm. This corresponds to the Entity field in the Alert Table in the database

alarmSeverity.name: alarmSeverity
alarmSeverity.description: This variable describes the severity of the alarm in integer format. This corresponds to the Severity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmPreviousSeverity.name: alarmPreviousSeverity
alarmPreviousSeverity.description: This variable states the previous severity of the alarm. This corresponds to the PreviousSeverity entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmCreateTime.name: alarmCreateTime
alarmCreateTime.description: This variable states the time at which the alarm has been created. This corresponds to the CreateTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmModTime.name: alarmModTime
alarmModTime.description: This variable states the latest time at which the alarm status was modified. This corresponds to the ModTime entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmCategory.name: alarmCategory
alarmCategory.description: This variable describes the category to which the alarm belongs to, in a string form. This corresponds to the Category entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmAssignedTo.name: alarmAssignedTo
alarmAssignedTo.description: This variable describes the owner to whom the alarm has assigned. This corresponds to the Who entry in the Alert Table in the database

alarmUserProperties.name: alarmUserProperties
alarmUserProperties.description: This variable describes the values of the user properties which the user specifies in the alertUserPropNames variable in the WebESMFaultMib module. The values will be displayed in the following format: userPropName1=value1,userPropName2=value2,...

numPollObjects.name: numPollObjects
numPollObjects.description: This variable displays the total number of PolledData objects currently present in the Polling engine.

numActivePollers.name: numActivePollers
numActivePollers.description: This variable displays the total number of active pollers at that time.

numThresholdObjects.name: numThresholdObjects
numThresholdObjects.description: This variable displays the total number of threshold objects available

pollid.name: pollid
pollid.description: This variable represents the id of the PolledData. It is assigned by the poll engine when the PolledData is created and it is a unique value for every PolledData.This corresponds to the Id entry in the PolledDataTable in the database

polldataName.name: polldataName
polldataName.description: This variable represents the name of the PolledData, which is a user assigned name for identification purposes.This corresponds to the Name entry in the PolledData Table in the database

oid.name: oid
oid.description: This variable represents the OID that is being polled for on the agent.This corresponds to the oid entry in the PolledData Table in the database

pollingInterval.name: pollingInterval
pollingInterval.description: This variable represents the polling interval of this PolledData.This corresponds to the Period entry in the PolledData Table in the database

failureCount.name: failureCount
failureCount.description: This variable represents the failureCount for this PolledData.This corresponds to the FailureCount entry in the PolledData Table in the database

failureThreshold.name: failureThreshold
failureThreshold.description: This variable represents the failureThreshold for this PolledData.This corresponds to the FailureThreshold entry in the PolledData Table in the database

timeToPoll.name: timeToPoll
timeToPoll.description: This variable states the time at which polling has to be done again.This corresponds to the TimeVal entry in the PolledData Table in the database

polledTime.name: polledTime
polledTime.description: This variable states the time at which the polling was done.This corresponds to the LastTimeValue entry in the PolledData Table in the database

pollTable.name: pollTable
pollTable.description: The table describes the polleddatas in the database

pollEntry.name: pollEntry
pollEntry.description: It describes the various entries of the performance table

agentName.name: agentName
agentName.description: This variable represents the Agent Name

thresholdObjectName.name: thresholdObjectName
thresholdObjectName.description: This variable states the name of the threshold object.

thresholdKind.name: thresholdKind
thresholdKind.description: This variable states whether the threshold is of type long,string or percentage.

thresholdMessage.name: thresholdMessage
thresholdMessage.description: This variable displays the message generated when the threshold occurs.

thresholdClearMessage.name: thresholdClearMessage
thresholdClearMessage.description: This variable displays the message to be generated on clearing of the threshold .

thresholdSeverity.name: thresholdSeverity
thresholdSeverity.description: The severity of the event generated.

thresholdCategory.name: thresholdCategory
thresholdCategory.description: This variable displays the category of this ThresholdObject. Category of the ThresholdObject represents the category in which the events will be generated in case of thresholds.

thresholdTable.name: thresholdTable
thresholdTable.description: A table showing all data related to threshold objects

thresholdEntry.name: thresholdEntry
thresholdEntry.description: All the entries of the threshold table

maxRows.name: maxRows
maxRows.description: This variable states the maximum number of rows that can be stored in the notilog table of the database.Once it exceeds the limit, the oldest row will be deleted from the database and the new row will be added.We can retrieve only that many number of rows from the notilog table as specified.

sequenceNum.name: sequenceNum
sequenceNum.description: This variable represents the index number of the last transmitted notification and is incremented by 1 whenever a notification is emitted from the agent. This would be included as a varbind for all notification.

notiLogIndex.name: notiLogIndex
notiLogIndex.description: This variable's purpose is to index the entries / distinguish the rows within this table. The value of this variable is the same as that of the sequenceNum defined in the mib. This table backs up all the transmitted notifications and facilitates selective recovery of lost notifications via their sequence numbers.

notiLogTime.name: notiLogTime
notiLogTime.description: This variable represents the value of sysUpTime when the entry occurred

notiLogNumVarBinds.name: notiLogNumVarBinds
notiLogNumVarBinds.description: This column indicates the number of variable bindings in the logged notification.

notiLogOid.name: notiLogOid
notiLogOid.description: This column indicates the OID of the Notification definition.

notiLogTable.name: notiLogTable
notiLogTable.description: This table contains the general information about the logged notifications.

notiLogEntry.name: notiLogEntry
notiLogEntry.description: An entry in the notiLog table.

varbindIndex.name: varbindIndex
varbindIndex.description: This variable's purpose is to provide the second level index to distinguish the entries / rows within this table. This value always starts at 1 and goes upto the maximum number of varbinds for a notification as indicated by in the notification log table.

varbindType.name: varbindType
varbindType.description: This specifies the type of the varbind that was sent as part of a Notification.

varbindValue.name: varbindValue
varbindValue.description: This variable provides the value of the corresponding varbind

varbindLogTable.name: varbindLogTable
varbindLogTable.description: This table contains the information of the varbinds sent during sending a notification. All the varbinds to the notifications are logged in this table except for the sequence number of the notification which serves as an index for this table.

varbindLogEntry.name: varbindLogEntry
varbindLogEntry.description: An entry in the Notification Log variable table.

serverName.name: serverName
serverName.description: This variable describes the name of the TFTP-server to or from which a file has to be sent or obtained

portNum.name: portNum
portNum.description: This variable states the port at which the file has to sent or obtained to or from the server respectively.

sourceFile.name: sourceFile
sourceFile.description: This variable states the name of the file to be obtained from the server [GET(1)] or sent to the server [PUT(2)].

destinationFile.name: destinationFile
destinationFile.description: This variable states the name of the file to be sent to the device [GET(1)] or obtained from the device [PUT(2)].

tftpMode.name: tftpMode
tftpMode.description: This variable states the mode of file-transfer

request.name: request
request.description: This variable states the operation to be performed .The operations that can be performed are: sending the file to a tftp server or getting a file from a tftp server. This variable takes two values indicating the type of operation performed. The value that this variable takes are :- (1) getting a file from a tftp server (2) sending a file to a tftp server

serialNumber.name: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: An incremental integer for the purpose of identifying the row

hostName.name: hostName
hostName.description: This states the DNS name or IpAddress of the device from which the value needs to be obtained

devicePort.name: devicePort
devicePort.description: The port of the device from which the value needs to be obtained

requestOid.name: requestOid
requestOid.description: This states the oid in the device whose value is needs to be obtained.

community.name: community
community.description: The community which may be specified.It is an optional field.If the community value is not specified,the default community 'public' will be taken

service.name: service
service.description: This variable takes two values ,1 and 2,which when set carry out SNMP operations: 1 for snmpGet 2 for snmpGetNext

result.name: result
result.description: This variable displays the result of the service :snmpGet/snmpGetNext of the specified oid in the specified device.If any of the specified data is not correct or if the host is not functioning properly then an exception Error in Data will be filled

proxyTable.name: proxyTable
proxyTable.description: This table is used to obtain the current value of an oid from a device .The values that the user needs to set are : IpAddress, Port,Community, OID and service. When the last value is set,the value for the oid is obtained

subAgentTable.name: subAgentTable
subAgentTable.description: The table having the details of sub-agents

subAgentoid.name: subAgentoid
subAgentoid.description: This states the oid of the sub-agent whose value is to be obtained from the sub-agent

subAgent.name: subAgent
subAgent.description: This variable states the sub-agent name to whom the request is sent.

subAgentPort.name: subAgentPort
subAgentPort.description: This states the sub- Agent's Port number at which the value has to be got.

subAgentCommunity.name: subAgentCommunity
subAgentCommunity.description: This specifies the sub- Agent community to which the request is sent.

timeout.name: timeout
timeout.description: This specifies the time period one has to wait for,to get a response from the sub agent.

rowStatus.name: rowStatus
rowStatus.description: This specifies the process by which the data have to be entered. This is the first value which needs to be set.. the value of 1 specifies 'active' the value of 2 specifies 'notInService' the value of 3 specifies 'notReady' the value of 4 specifies 'createAndGo'. the value of 5 specifies 'createAndWait' the value of 6 specifies 'destroy'

v1v2TrapForwardingTable.name: v1v2TrapForwardingTable
v1v2TrapForwardingTable.description: This table maintains the SNMP v1 and v2c managers information like manager IP address, port number,community, time out, retires, etc which are used in trap generation. Timeout and retires are used in the case of SNMPv2c INFORM.

v1v2TrapForwardingEntry.name: v1v2TrapForwardingEntry
v1v2TrapForwardingEntry.description: Each entry in this table refers one manager information who is registered to receive traps fromt the agent.

v1v2ManagerHost.name: v1v2ManagerHost
v1v2ManagerHost.description: IP address where the manager is listening to receive traps from the agent.

v1v2ManagerPort.name: v1v2ManagerPort
v1v2ManagerPort.description: The port at which manager is listening for the traps from the agent.

v1v2ManagerCommunity.name: v1v2ManagerCommunity
v1v2ManagerCommunity.description: The community used by the agent to send trap or inform to this manager.

v1v2ManagerTimeOut.name: v1v2ManagerTimeOut
v1v2ManagerTimeOut.description: The time out value in seconds for SNMPv2c INFORM.

v1v2ManagerRetries.name: v1v2ManagerRetries
v1v2ManagerRetries.description: The number of retries in the case of SNMPV2c INFORM.

v1v2ManagerStatus.name: v1v2ManagerStatus
v1v2ManagerStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the usmUserStatus column is 'notReady'

v3TrapForwardingTable.name: v3TrapForwardingTable
v3TrapForwardingTable.description: This table maintains the SNMP v3 managers information like manager IP address, port number, user name,security model, context name, community, time out,retires, etc which are used in trap generation. Timeout and retires are used in the case of INFORM.

v3TrapForwardingEntry.name: v3TrapForwardingEntry
v3TrapForwardingEntry.description: Each entry in this table refers one SNMPv3 manager who will listen for TRAP or INFORM.

v3ManagerHost.name: v3ManagerHost
v3ManagerHost.description: The IP address where the manager is listening for TRAPS or INFORMS.

v3ManagerPort.name: v3ManagerPort
v3ManagerPort.description: The UDP port at which manager is listening for TRAPS or INFORMS.

v3ManagerCommunity.name: v3ManagerCommunity
v3ManagerCommunity.description: The community string used by the agent when sending SNMP v1/v2c TRAPS or INFORMS to the manager.It used to support backward compatability,i.e. without any change in the table,user can send both SNMPv1 and v2c TARPS and INFORMS.

v3ManagerUserName.name: v3ManagerUserName
v3ManagerUserName.description: This user name is same as in USM MIB RFC 2574.

v3ManagerUserSecModel.name: v3ManagerUserSecModel
v3ManagerUserSecModel.description: This security model value is same as in USM table of USM MIB RFC2574.

v3ManagerUserContextName.name: v3ManagerUserContextName
v3ManagerUserContextName.description: This context name is same as in VacmAccessTable of VACM MIB RFC2575.

v3ManagerTimeOut.name: v3ManagerTimeOut
v3ManagerTimeOut.description: The time out value in seconds for INFORM request.

v3ManagerRetries.name: v3ManagerRetries
v3ManagerRetries.description: The number of retries for a failed INFORM reqeust.

v3ManagerStatus.name: v3ManagerStatus
v3ManagerStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the usmUserStatus column is 'notReady'

httpPort.name: httpPort
httpPort.description: This describes the http port.This port can be used to open an html client connection to the WWP ESM Server

rmiRegistryPort.name: rmiRegistryPort
rmiRegistryPort.description: This describes the RMI-Registry port.This port can be used to open a RMI client connection to the WWP ESM Server

trapPortTable.name: trapPortTable
trapPortTable.description: This table describes the ports at which the traps are being received by the WWP ESM

trapPortEntry.name: trapPortEntry
trapPortEntry.description: It describes an entry in the trap-port table

moExtraPropNames.name: moExtraPropNames
moExtraPropNames.description: The extra properties which the user wants to be sent with the pre-defined notificaiton varbinds. It should be in the following format. SYNTAX: propName1,propName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: propName1=value1,propName2=value2...

ismExtraPropNames.name: ismExtraPropNames
ismExtraPropNames.description: The extra properties which the user wants to be sent with the pre-defined notificaiton varbinds. It should be in the following format. SYNTAX: propName1,propName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: propName1=value1,propName2=value2...

alertExtraPropNames.name: alertExtraPropNames
alertExtraPropNames.description: The extra properties which the user wants to be sent with the pre-defined notificaiton varbinds. It should be in the following format. SYNTAX: propName1,propName2,... The values for the properties will be in the following format: propName1=value1,propName2=value2..

statsdataTableName.name: statsdataTableName
statsdataTableName.description: This variable states the name of the table of the statsdata table, the details of which,the user wants to view.The user needs to enter values in the form of statsdata% or statsdataMM_DD_YY.If the user gives statsdata%,then the current day is taken.

pollID.name: pollID
pollID.description: This variable states the id value of the polldata

time.name: time
time.description: This variable states the time at which the data was collected

oidindex.name: oidindex
oidindex.description: This variable states the instance of the collected data

value.name: value
value.description: This variable states the value of the collected data

statsDataTable.name: statsDataTable
statsDataTable.description: This table exposes the statsdata table of the database for the day

statsDataEntry.name: statsDataEntry
statsDataEntry.description: Each entry contains the data like time,oidindex and value for a particular pollid

autoDiscover.name: autoDiscover
autoDiscover.description: This variable takes integer values like 1 for true and 2 for false.This variable states whether the auto discovery process should start or not

discoverLocalNet.name: discoverLocalNet
discoverLocalNet.description: This variable states whether the local network should be discovered or not

discoverInterval.name: discoverInterval
discoverInterval.description: The time interval in which the discovery process should occur

enablelog.name: enablelog
enablelog.description: This variable states whether the logging should be enabled or not

networkDiscoveryIndex.name: networkDiscoveryIndex
networkDiscoveryIndex.description: This variable states the index of the network discovery table

netIPAddress.name: netIPAddress
netIPAddress.description: This variable states the ipaddress of the network which has to be discovered

netMask.name: netMask
netMask.description: This provides for the net-mask of the network to be discovered

startIPAddress.name: startIPAddress
startIPAddress.description: This variable states the ipaddress from which the discovery process should start for the network

endIPAddress.name: endIPAddress
endIPAddress.description: This variable states the ipaddress till which the discovery process should proceed for the network

doDiscovery.name: doDiscovery
doDiscovery.description: This variable states whether a particular network should be discovered or not

dhcp.name: dhcp
dhcp.description: This variable states whether the network supports DHCP or not

networkDiscoveryTable.name: networkDiscoveryTable
networkDiscoveryTable.description: This table stores the criteria for the discovery of networks in the ESM

networkDiscoveryEntry.name: networkDiscoveryEntry
networkDiscoveryEntry.description: Each entry states the discovery criteria for a network

nodeIP.name: nodeIP
nodeIP.description: This variable states the ipaddress of the node to be discovered

nodeNetMask.name: nodeNetMask
nodeNetMask.description: This variable states the net mask for the discovery of the node

nodeDiscoverEnable.name: nodeDiscoverEnable
nodeDiscoverEnable.description: This variable states whether a particular node should be discovered or not

snmpAgentPort.name: snmpAgentPort
snmpAgentPort.description: This variable states the port at which the snmp agent is listening

nodeCommunity.name: nodeCommunity
nodeCommunity.description: This variable states the community of the node to be discovered

snmpVersion.name: snmpVersion
snmpVersion.description: This variable states the version of snmp

v3UserName.name: v3UserName
v3UserName.description: This variable states the v3userName. If the snmp version is v3 then the user name has to be given to access the node

v3ContextName.name: v3ContextName
v3ContextName.description: This variable states the v3contextName. If the snmp version is v3 then the context name has to be given to access the node

nodeDiscoveryTable.name: nodeDiscoveryTable
nodeDiscoveryTable.description: This table contains the node discovery criteria

nodeDiscoveryEntry.name: nodeDiscoveryEntry
nodeDiscoveryEntry.description: `This contains the entry of NodeDiscTable which has the criteria for discovery of a node

criteriaIndex.name: criteriaIndex
criteriaIndex.description: This variable uniquely identifies each entry of the table

propertyName.name: propertyName
propertyName.description: This variable states the property name on which basis the discovery should be done

propertyValue.name: propertyValue
propertyValue.description: This variable states the value for a property,on which basis discovery should be done

allow.name: allow
allow.description: This variable states whether the criteria for discovery should be considered or not

moCriteriaTable.name: moCriteriaTable
moCriteriaTable.description: This table contains the various criteria for discovery in order to further refine the search

moCriteriaEntry.name: moCriteriaEntry
moCriteriaEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains some criteria for making the discovery process further refined

discFilterIndex.name: discFilterIndex
discFilterIndex.description: An incremental integer for uniquely identifying each element of the table

discFilterClassName.name: discFilterClassName
discFilterClassName.description: This variable states the class Name of the discovery filter file

discoveryFilterTable.name: discoveryFilterTable
discoveryFilterTable.description: This table has the discovery filter class names

discoveryFilterEntry.name: discoveryFilterEntry
discoveryFilterEntry.description: Each entry of this table has the discovery filter class name

trapFilterIndex.name: trapFilterIndex
trapFilterIndex.description: The user defined name for the trap filter

alertFilterClassName.name: alertFilterClassName
alertFilterClassName.description: The class name of the trap filter

trapFilterName.name: trapFilterName
trapFilterName.description: This variable states the name of the trap filter

trapFilterEnable.name: trapFilterEnable
trapFilterEnable.description: This variable states if the trap filter should be enabled or not

enterpriseOID.name: enterpriseOID
enterpriseOID.description: When the snmp version is v3,this variable needs to be stated

trapOID.name: trapOID
trapOID.description: This variable states the oid of the trap to be sent

setFilter.name: setFilter
setFilter.description: 0: Do nothing 1: To set trap filter

trapFilterTable.name: trapFilterTable
trapFilterTable.description: This table states the class names of the various trap filters

trapFilterEntry.name: trapFilterEntry
trapFilterEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains the name of the class of a trap filter

pollingFilterIndex.name: pollingFilterIndex
pollingFilterIndex.description: An incremental integer to uniquely identify each entry of the table

pollingFilterClassName.name: pollingFilterClassName
pollingFilterClassName.description: This variable states the class names of the polling filters used

pollingFiltersEntry.name: pollingFiltersEntry
pollingFiltersEntry.description: Each entry of the table contains a poll-filter

logIndex.name: logIndex
logIndex.description: This is an incremental integer which uniquely identifies each entry of the table

logFileName.name: logFileName
logFileName.description: This variable states the file name of the log file

logDirName.name: logDirName
logDirName.description: This variable states the directory name of the log file

maxLines.name: maxLines
maxLines.description: This variable states the number of lines that can be stored in a single file

maxFiles.name: maxFiles
maxFiles.description: This variable states the number of files of the same type can be formed

linesCached.name: linesCached
linesCached.description: This variable states the number of lines that can be cached

timeStamp.name: timeStamp
timeStamp.description: This variable states whether time-stamping need be done or not

logTable.name: logTable
logTable.description: This table contains data regarding the logging of values

logEntry.name: logEntry
logEntry.description: Each entry of this table states the log name and the data regarding its storage

logUserIndex.name: logUserIndex
logUserIndex.description: An incremental integer which uniquely identifies each entry of the table

logUserName.name: logUserName
logUserName.description: This variable states the name of the log user

displayName.name: displayName
displayName.description: This variable states the name which is displayed for each log user

logLevel.name: logLevel
logLevel.description: This variable states the level at which the logging needs to be done

enableLog.name: enableLog
enableLog.description: This variable states whether logging should be enabled or not

logUserTable.name: logUserTable
logUserTable.description: This table states the name of the log users

logUserEntry.name: logUserEntry
logUserEntry.description: Each entry of the table states the user name and the display name of the file

moEnrolNotification.name: moEnrolNotification
moEnrolNotification.description: The ESMAgent sends a moEnrolNotification to the manager when an MO has been enrolled/added into management domain.

moDeenrolNotification.name: moDeenrolNotification
moDeenrolNotification.description: The ESMAgent sends a moDeenrolNotification to the manager when an MO has been deenrolled/deleted from the management domain

moAttrChangeNotification.name: moAttrChangeNotification
moAttrChangeNotification.description: The ESMAgent sends a moAttrChangeNotification to the manager when any discoverd MO's one or more attributes are changed.

moName.name: moName
moName.description: This variable indicates the name of the MO.

moownerName.name: moownerName
moownerName.description: This variable represents the Ownername of the Network Element. This name also uniquely represents the MO in the network domain across all MO types.

moNodeType.name: moNodeType
moNodeType.description: This variable describes the type of the MO ie whether it is node, motwork,interface,etc.

moEnrolTime.name: moEnrolTime
moEnrolTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the MO was formally enrolled in the management domain

moDeEnrolTime.name: moDeEnrolTime
moDeEnrolTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the MO was formally deenrolled in the management domain

moDataChangeTime.name: moDataChangeTime
moDataChangeTime.description: This variable indicates when a particular value's time of change is formally acknowleged by the ESM.

moExtraProperties.name: moExtraProperties
moExtraProperties.description: The values for the user properties which the user specifies in the moExtraPropNames variable are sent as part of the notifications The values will be displayed in the folloing formate propName1=value1,porpName2=vaule2,....

moIpAddress.name: moIpAddress
moIpAddress.description: This variable provides the IP address of the device that this topology event relates to.

moIpAddressAddrType.name: moIpAddressAddrType
moIpAddressAddrType.description: This variable provides the IP Address type of the device that this topology event relates to

moIpAddressAddr.name: moIpAddressAddr
moIpAddressAddr.description: This variable provides the IPV4 or the IPV6 address of the device that this topology event relates to

ismStateChangeNotification.name: ismStateChangeNotification
ismStateChangeNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismStateChangeNotification to the manager when the state of service created in ISM has changed.

ismNodeChangeNotification.name: ismNodeChangeNotification
ismNodeChangeNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismNodeChangeNotification to the manager when the config on the node in ISM has changed.

ismNotification.name: ismNotification
ismNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismNotification to the manager with ISM related information.

ismBadParameterNotification.name: ismBadParameterNotification
ismBadParameterNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismBadParameterNotification to the manager whenever a bad parameter is passed to ISM.

ismConstraintViolationNotification.name: ismConstraintViolationNotification
ismConstraintViolationNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismConstraintViolationNotification to the manager whenever constraints are violated within ISM.

ismMisconfigurationDetectedNotification.name: ismMisconfigurationDetectedNotification
ismMisconfigurationDetectedNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismMisconfigurationDetectedNotification to the manager whenever ISM detects a misconfiguratiomn in the network.

ismUnsupportedConfigurationNotification.name: ismUnsupportedConfigurationNotification
ismUnsupportedConfigurationNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismUnsupportedConfigurationNotification to the manager whenever ISM detects a unsupported configuration in the network.

ismInvalidPathSelectionNotification.name: ismInvalidPathSelectionNotification
ismInvalidPathSelectionNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismInvalidPathSelectionNotification to the manager whenever ISM detects that an invalid path is selected.

ismModifyNotification.name: ismModifyNotification
ismModifyNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends a ismModifyNotification to the manager to report the status of modify request sent to ISM

currentState.name: currentState
currentState.description: This variable indicates the current state of the service.

previousState.name: previousState
previousState.description: This variable indicates the previous state of the service.

uniqueIdentifier.name: uniqueIdentifier
uniqueIdentifier.description: This variable indicates the unique identifer of the service.

stateChangeTime.name: stateChangeTime
stateChangeTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the state of the service changed.

statsCounters.name: statsCounters
statsCounters.description: This variable contains the various stats counter of the service if available.The values will be displayed in the folloing formate propName1=value1,porpName2=vaule2,....

nodeChangeTime.name: nodeChangeTime
nodeChangeTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the config on the node has changed.

text.name: text
text.description: This variable gives the descriptive text message of the event.This corresponds to the Text entry in the Event Table in the database

node.name: node
node.description: This variable indicates the node on which config has changed.

ismExtraProperties.name: ismExtraProperties
ismExtraProperties.description: The values for the user properties which the user specifies in the moExtraPropNames variable are sent as part of the notifications The values will be displayed in the folloing formate propName1=value1,porpName2=vaule2,....

notifTime.name: notifTime
notifTime.description: This variable represents the time at which the notification was generated

status.name: status
status.description: This variable indicates the status of a request.

alertCriticalNotification.name: alertCriticalNotification
alertCriticalNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends an alertCriticalNotification to the manager indicating that an alert of 'Critical' severity has been raised on a MO

alertMajorNotification.name: alertMajorNotification
alertMajorNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends an alertMajorNotification to the manager indicating that an alert of 'Major' severity has been raised on a MO

alertMinorNotification.name: alertMinorNotification
alertMinorNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends an alertMinorNotification to the manager indicating that an alert of 'Minor' severity has been raised on a MO

alertWarningNotification.name: alertWarningNotification
alertWarningNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends an alertWarningNotification to the manager indicating that an alert of 'Warning' severity has been raised on a MO

alertClearNotification.name: alertClearNotification
alertClearNotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends an alertClearNotification to the manager indicating that one or more previously reported alerts have been cleared

alertCustomNBINotification.name: alertCustomNBINotification
alertCustomNBINotification.description: The ESM-Agent sends an alertCustomNBINotification to the manager for every SNMP v1 or v2 notification received from the device

alertentity.name: alertentity
alertentity.description: This variable states the unique source of the alert which uniquely identifies any alert in the table

alertownerName.name: alertownerName
alertownerName.description: This variable states the name of the owner of the alert

alertTimeStamp.name: alertTimeStamp
alertTimeStamp.description: This variable indicates the time at which the alert was last modified

alertNotificationId.name: alertNotificationId
alertNotificationId.description: This variable indicates the id of the generated alert

alertcategory.name: alertcategory
alertcategory.description: This variable provides a string representation of the category of the alert

alertExtraProperties.name: alertExtraProperties
alertExtraProperties.description: The values for the user properties which the user specifies in the alertExtraPropNames variable are sent as part of the notifications The values will be displayed in the following format: propName1=value1,propName2=vaule2,....

alertIpAddress.name: alertIpAddress
alertIpAddress.description: This variable provides the IP address of the device that this alert relates to.

alertEmsTime.name: alertEmsTime
alertEmsTime.description: Default value indicates the sysUpTime of ESM.

alertNeTime.name: alertNeTime
alertNeTime.description: Default value indicates the sysUpTime of source of this alarm.

alertEmsName.name: alertEmsName
alertEmsName.description: Default value indicates the system name of ESM. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertNeNodeId.name: alertNeNodeId
alertNeNodeId.description: Default value indicates the system name (IP address) of source of this alarm. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertObjectType.name: alertObjectType
alertObjectType.description: Default value indicates the type of managed object that this trap refers to. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertObjectName.name: alertObjectName
alertObjectName.description: Default value indicates the name of managed object that this trap refers to. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertseverity.name: alertseverity
alertseverity.description: Default value indicates the severity of the forwarded trap.Possible values: none, Clear, Intermediate, Critical, Major, Minor, Warning, Config, Info, Debug, Internal. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertServiceAffecting.name: alertServiceAffecting
alertServiceAffecting.description: Default value indicates if this trap is service affecting.Possible values: true,false. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertProbableCauseDescription.name: alertProbableCauseDescription
alertProbableCauseDescription.description: Default value indicates probable cause of notification received from device.Possible values: as defined in IANAItuProbableCause (IANA-ITU-ALARM-TC-MIB) Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertAdditionalText.name: alertAdditionalText
alertAdditionalText.description: Default value indicates additional text describing alarm being raised. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertEventType.name: alertEventType
alertEventType.description: Default value indicates event type describing alarm being raised.Possible values: as defined in IANAItuEventType (IANA-ITU-ALARM-TC-MIB). Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertNeNodeName.name: alertNeNodeName
alertNeNodeName.description: Default value indicates the system name (DNS name if available, IP address if name cannot be resolved) of source of this alarm. Content may vary specific to customer deployments and as defined by trap customizer feature of ESM.

alertIpAddressAddrType.name: alertIpAddressAddrType
alertIpAddressAddrType.description: This variable provides the IP Address type of the device that this alert relates to

alertIpAddressAddr.name: alertIpAddressAddr
alertIpAddressAddr.description: This variable provides the V4/V6 IP Address of the device that this alert relates to

eventid.name: eventid
eventid.description: This variable is the unique id (primary key) of this event object.

eventsource.name: eventsource
eventsource.description: This variable is the source of the event

eventEntity.name: eventEntity
eventEntity.description: This variable is the Entity (also known as Failure Object) of the Event.
